---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Character of the Guesthouse — Mas du Chanoine" description="The spirit of Mas du Chanoine: friendliness, personalized welcome, Provençal decoration and discovery of the French Riviera." lang="en">
  <section class="relative h-[50vh] min-h-[400px] flex items-end overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-primary-950/70 via-primary-950/30 to-primary-950/10 z-10"></div>
    <img src="/media/esprit/chambres-hotes.jpg" alt="The warm and Provençal spirit of Mas du Chanoine" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" loading="eager" />
    <div class="relative z-20 text-white px-4 md:px-8 pb-12 max-w-4xl">
      <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-3 text-primary-200 font-light">Our philosophy</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-semibold leading-tight">Character of the Guesthouse</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent-600 mb-3 font-medium">Welcome</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-semibold mb-6 text-primary-900 leading-tight">Guest Rooms & Family Suite</h2>
        <div class="prose-content text-base md:text-lg">
          <p>Welcome to the French Riviera, to the Mas du Chanoine where we will welcome you with great pleasure in our country house of unique character for your getaway weekends or your longer stays. We offer three guest rooms of refined elegance as well as one family suite.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad bg-primary-50">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent-600 mb-3 font-medium">At your service</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-semibold mb-6 text-primary-900 leading-tight">Friendliness & Discovery of Provence</h2>
        <div class="prose-content text-base md:text-lg">
          <p>We are at your service to make your stay on the French Riviera as perfect as unforgettable. Upon your arrival at the Mas du Chanoine, you will be overwhelmed by the friendliness of our welcome: after becoming acquainted with your room and the different areas of the property, we will join you over a welcome drink and we will suggest, according to your interests, a palette of things to do, places to visit or restaurants to book.</p><p>During your stay, we will remain available to help you plan your days, your reservations. We are there to assist you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent-600 mb-3 font-medium">Lounge & Reading</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-semibold mb-6 text-primary-900 leading-tight">Library & Documentation on the French Riviera</h2>
        <div class="prose-content text-base md:text-lg">
          <p>Our wish is for this guest house to be an open house for our guests. You are welcome at any time to admire the stained glass in the piano lounge, consult the documentation on the French Riviera as well as the numerous books about Provence (its landscapes, artists, museums, etc.) in the library.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad bg-primary-50">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent-600 mb-3 font-medium">Art & Decoration</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-semibold mb-6 text-primary-900 leading-tight">Provence & Artists</h2>
        <div class="prose-content text-base md:text-lg">
          <p>The entire Mas is decorated according to the traditions of Provence where you will find painted furniture, two fireplaces in Vence limestone, two stained glass windows made by Hans Erni (renowned Swiss artist who lived in Saint-Paul de Vence) and Jacques Fonmarty (master art glass maker in Saint-Paul de Vence).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad bg-primary-900 text-white text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-semibold mb-4">Experience the spirit of the Mas</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-300 mb-8 text-lg">Book your stay and discover the French Riviera differently.</p>
      <a href="https://masduchanoine.thais-hotel.com/hotel/website/reservations.php?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary bg-white text-primary-900 hover:bg-primary-100">Book now</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
